cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.MA, cs.NE, cs.SI 

The paper deals with consensus-based synchronization of multi-agent systems, which is a topic in control theory and falls under the cs.SY (Systems and Control) category. The use of H ∞ transient consensus and gain scheduling also suggests a focus on optimization and machine learning, which are covered by cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) categories. The use of interpolation and continuous coefficients suggests a focus on numerical methods, which is covered by cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) category. Finally, the application to synchronization of uncertain bilinear systems suggests a focus on nonlinear systems, which is covered by cs.SI (Systems and Information Theory) category.
